8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 730, L.D. 1860, “An Act to Allow
10 Certain Distributed Energy Resources to Participate in the State's Net Energy Billing
11 Program”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Allow for a Competitive Solicitation of Energy Projects Under 5
14 Megawatts'
15 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency preamble.
16 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
17 following:
18 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3210-K is enacted to read:
19 §3210-K. Distributed generation resource procurement; mechanical completion
20 1. Definitions. As used in this section, the following terms have the following
21 meanings.
22 A. "Distributed generation resource" has the same meaning as in section 3209‑A,
23 subsection 1, paragraph B.
24 B. "Eligible generator" means a distributed generation resource with a nameplate
25 capacity of less than 5 megawatts that reached mechanical completion before January
26 1, 2025.
27 C. "Mechanical completion" means, with respect to a distributed generation resource,
28 fully physically constructed and ready for operation.
29 2. Competitive procurement. The commission shall direct investor-owned
30 transmission and distribution utilities to enter into one or more contracts for energy or
31 renewable energy credits or both from eligible generators in accordance with this section.
32 The commission may not require an eligible generator to contract for the sale of energy or
33 renewable energy credits under this section.
Page 1 - 132LR2109(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 730, L.D. 1860
1 A. By November 1, 2025, the commission shall initiate a competitive solicitation for
2 contracts under this section for energy or renewable energy credits or both in an amount
3 determined by the commission.
4 B. The commission may not award a contract to an eligible generator at a rate that
5 exceeds 65% of the tariff rate calculated under section 3209-B, subsection 5, paragraph
6 A-1 applicable on January 1, 2025 to medium commercial customers or industrial
7 customers in the transmission and distribution service territory in which the eligible
8 generator is located.
9 3. Contract terms. A contract entered into pursuant to this section must be for a term
10 of no more than 20 years, unless the commission finds a contract for a longer term to be
11 prudent.
12 4. Rules. The commission may adopt rules to implement this section. Rules adopted
13 in accordance with this subsection are routine technical rules pursuant to Title 5, chapter
14 375, subchapter 2‑A.'
15 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
16 number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment replaces the bill, changes the title and removes the emergency
1199 preamble and clause. It requires the Public Utilities Commission, by November 1, 2025,
2200 to initiate a competitive solicitation for contracts for energy or renewable energy credits or
2211 both from distributed generation resources with a nameplate capacity of less than 5
2222 megawatts that have reached mechanical completion before January 1, 2025. The
2233 commission may not award a contract at a rate that exceeds 65% of the tariff rate calculated
2244 under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 35-A, section 3209-B, subsection 5, paragraph A-1
2255 applicable on January 1, 2025 to medium commercial customers or industrial customers in
2266 the transmission and distribution service territory in which the eligible generator is located.
2277 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2288 (See attached)
